form_title.ms_form_title_llm_v1: U.S. Department of Justice Immigration and Naturalization Service, I-102, I-129, I-129F, I-129S, I-130, I-539, I-730, I-589, I-765, I-131

full_text: Screened by NARA, 8/11/2023 The following applications must be sent to the Eastern Service Center, using the Post Office box numbers and Zip Codes as listed: I-102 P.O. Box 9102 05479-9102 I-129, I-129F, I-129S P.O. Box 9129 05479-9129 I-130 P.O. Box 9130 05479-9130 1-539 P.O. Box 9539 05479-9539 Mail these applications to: U.S. Department of Justice Immigration and Naturalization Service Eastern Service Center P.O. Box (Insert correct box number listed above) St. Albans, VT (Insert correct Zip Code listed-above) The I-730, I-589 Application, and concurrently submitted I-765, must be mailed to the Southern Service Center at: U.S. Department of Justice Immigration and Naturalization Service Southern Service Center P.O. Box 82521 Irving, TX 75016-2122 Application I-131 (other than advance parole to return to U.S.) must be mailed to the Northern Service Center at: U.S. Department of Justice Immigration and Naturalization Service Northern Service Center P.O. Box 87131 Lincoln, NE 68501-7131 Failure to use the correct address will delay the processing of your application. Washington Immigration Information may be obtained by calling (202) 307-1501.
